{
  "stem": "5551.2",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The first killing I witnessed is when I was sick with pneumonia.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "In those days, this was late in 1941, I came down with pneumonia.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And in those days, pneumonia was a deathly disease.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I had just gotten a little better.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "My family was still intact.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "It was a Saturday afternoon, beautiful day.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "I remember it like today.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "It was a-- it was-- it might have been in-- in September or so of 1941.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "A group of Germans, apparently the sonderkommando, came into town and started shooting Jewish people, at random, in the street.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "As I looked out the window, Jews were running.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And Germans were having great fun target shooting.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "I believe we had eight casualties that day.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "Most of them were senile or-- or mentally impaired people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "One of them was an 18-year-old child that I remember.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Pardon me, I'm wrong.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "An eight-year-old child, that I remember.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "The others were older and many of them mentally impaired people.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "I remember this as the first time that I saw open murder in the street.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "This brings me to your question.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "My reaction was of horror, of course.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "But even though we witnessed these kind of horrifying incidents-- by now, outright, open murder-- still, when we heard from others the horrifying descriptions of what went on in-- in ghettos that were liquidated, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] we-- we simply lacked the-- the-- the fantasy to perceive what that means, to-- to understand this.",
      "word_count": 55
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "We couldn't believe that such a thing is-- is conceivable.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] One of the things that-- the German brutality and subhuman behavior was of such magnitude that it didn't-- it didn't square well with the normal human mind.",
      "word_count": 31
    }
  ],
